# ntfy Authentication Configuration
# FR-066: ntfy認証対応
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy this file to config/ntfy_auth.env
#   2. Fill in your credentials
#   3. config/ntfy_auth.env is NOT tracked by git (whitelist .gitignore)
#
# NOTE: The public ntfy.sh instance does NOT support authentication.
#       Token/Basic auth requires a self-hosted ntfy server.
#       See: https://docs.ntfy.sh/config/#access-control

# --- Bearer Token Auth (recommended for self-hosted ntfy) ---
# Generate with: ntfy token add <username>
# Format: tk_ followed by 29 alphanumeric chars
# NTFY_TOKEN=tk_your_token_here

# --- Basic Auth (alternative for self-hosted ntfy) ---
# NTFY_USER=your_username
# NTFY_PASS=your_password

# Priority: Token > Basic > None
# If neither is set, no auth headers are sent (backward compatible with public ntfy.sh)
